  "elapsed_s": 272.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And then I finally-- I managed to whip out the certificate that was given to me by the military governor in Feldafing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And when he looked at it, he finally told me to get back on the boat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And so I left-- it must have been in-- in the last week or so of December from Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And I arrived actually at the shores of the United States sometime in late December and was cooling my heels maybe for a week or so-- two-- I don't even know exactly how much time passed-- just outside Coney Island, in New York, where 120 ships [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] were waiting for-- to be-- for berths, so that they can discharge the soldiers and-- and, you know, bring the boys home for Christmas.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "So that by the time I actually was admitted to the United States and, so to say, stepped on the ground of United States, it was January 6, 1946.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And my-- at-- at that time my brother-in-law, who was still in the uniform of the American Merchant Marine and my sister, who was married to him, picked me up and-- and I suppose must have whisked me through the customs, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And there I was in America.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And-- and that was on a Thursday, I remember.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And on Sunday morning, I went to work for the Zionist Organization of America.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And my saying that perhaps doesn't quite convey what I really want to say, which is that I had [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] no problem really surviving survival, unlike some other people.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "I had accepted my survival, and-- because I had a purpose and a goal.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
